checklist_comments: observers=Haven Wiley; others=Minna Wiley; vehicles=15; habitat@1R=BB (formerly P); weather=70-75F, overcast becoming clear, no wind; notes=BHVI in pines with reduced understory as usual; no CWWI nor EWPW at stop 1R (both formerly regular here before habitat changed to B this year); CWWI heard at stop 3L (where occasionally heard formerly); EWPW heard 1.0 miles north of stop 1 (see pre-count on this date); BHVI singing in pine flatwoods (tall pines managed to reduce understory) in same habitat and same general location where it has occurred on these censuses for the past 20 years!
notes: BHVI in pines with reduced understory as usual

loc: MBBS, NC, Chatham Co, Route 03, Bonsal Crossroad
checklist_comments: observers=Haven Wiley; others=Minna Wiley; vehicles=7; habitat@11=SS (formerly PP), @12=SS (formerly PP); weather=70F, thick overcast, no wind; notes=large area along Moncure Flatwood Road, formerly mature pines, had been clearcut, but with remaining seed trees and scattered shrubs; no CWWI nor EWPW at stop 1 nor during 3 pre-count stops (both formerly regular here); EASO and GHOW heard at one of 3 pre-count stops; LOSH singing on Christian Chapel Church Rd (0.4 mile south of old US1) from trees in and beside large grassy field; no BHVI at stop 12 (formerly regular here before clear-cutting); this year is the first with hearing aids, which increased detection of distant birds and BGGN

loc: MBBS, NC, Chatham Co, Route 03, Bonsal Crossroad
checklist_comments: observers=Haven Wiley; others=Minna Wiley; vehicles=15; habitat@1R=BB (formerly P); weather=70-75F, overcast becoming clear, no wind; notes=BHVI in pines with reduced understory as usual; no CWWI nor EWPW at stop 1R (both formerly regular here before habitat changed to B this year); CWWI heard at stop 3L (where occasionally heard formerly); EWPW heard 1.0 miles north of stop 1 (see pre-count on this date); BHVI singing in pine flatwoods (tall pines managed to reduce understory) in same habitat and same general location where it has occurred on these censuses for the past 20 years!
notes: BHVI in pines with reduced understory as usual

loc: MBBS, NC, Chatham Co, Route 03, Bonsal Crossroad
checklist_comments: observers=Haven Wiley; others=Minna Wiley; vehicles=7; habitat@11=SS (formerly PP), @12=SS (formerly PP); weather=70F, thick overcast, no wind; notes=large area along Moncure Flatwood Road, formerly mature pines, had been clearcut, but with remaining seed trees and scattered shrubs; no CWWI nor EWPW at stop 1 nor during 3 pre-count stops (both formerly regular here); EASO and GHOW heard at one of 3 pre-count stops; LOSH singing on Christian Chapel Church Rd (0.4 mile south of old US1) from trees in and beside large grassy field; no BHVI at stop 12 (formerly regular here before clear-cutting); this year is the first with hearing aids, which increased detection of distant birds and BGGN
notes: large area along Moncure Flatwood Road, formerly mature pines, had been clearcut, but with remaining seed trees and scattered shrubs

checklist_comments: observers=Haven Wiley; others=Minna Wiley; vehicles=15; habitat@1R=BB (formerly P); weather=70-75F, overcast becoming clear, no wind; notes=BHVI in pines with reduced understory as usual; no CWWI nor EWPW at stop 1R (both formerly regular here before habitat changed to B this year); CWWI heard at stop 3L (where occasionally heard formerly); EWPW heard 1.0 miles north of stop 1 (see pre-count on this date); BHVI singing in pine flatwoods (tall pines managed to reduce understory) in same habitat and same general location where it has occurred on these censuses for the past 20 years!

loc: MBBS, NC, Chatham Co, Route 03, Bonsal Crossroad
checklist_comments: observers=Haven Wiley; others=Minna Wiley; vehicles=7; habitat@11=SS (formerly PP), @12=SS (formerly PP); weather=70F, thick overcast, no wind; notes=large area along Moncure Flatwood Road, formerly mature pines, had been clearcut, but with remaining seed trees and scattered shrubs; no CWWI nor EWPW at stop 1 nor during 3 pre-count stops (both formerly regular here); EASO and GHOW heard at one of 3 pre-count stops; LOSH singing on Christian Chapel Church Rd (0.4 mile south of old US1) from trees in and beside large grassy field; no BHVI at stop 12 (formerly regular here before clear-cutting); this year is the first with hearing aids, which increased detection of distant birds and BGGN
notes: large area along Moncure Flatwood Road, formerly mature pines, had been clearcut, but with remaining seed trees and scattered shrubs

loc: MBBS, NC, Chatham Co, Route 03, Bonsal Crossroad
checklist_comments: observers=Haven Wiley; others=Minna Wiley; vehicles=15; habitat@1R=BB (formerly P); weather=70-75F, overcast becoming clear, no wind; notes=BHVI in pines with reduced understory as usual; no CWWI nor EWPW at stop 1R (both formerly regular here before habitat changed to B this year); CWWI heard at stop 3L (where occasionally heard formerly); EWPW heard 1.0 miles north of stop 1 (see pre-count on this date); BHVI singing in pine flatwoods (tall pines managed to reduce understory) in same habitat and same general location where it has occurred on these censuses for the past 20 years!
notes: BHVI in pines with reduced understory as usual

loc: MBBS, NC, Chatham Co, Route 03, Bonsal Crossroad
checklist_comments: observers=Haven Wiley; others=Minna Wiley; vehicles=7; habitat@11=SS (formerly PP), @12=SS (formerly PP); weather=70F, thick overcast, no wind; notes=large area along Moncure Flatwood Road, formerly mature pines, had been clearcut, but with remaining seed trees and scattered shrubs; no CWWI nor EWPW at stop 1 nor during 3 pre-count stops (both formerly regular here); EASO and GHOW heard at one of 3 pre-count stops; LOSH singing on Christian Chapel Church Rd (0.4 mile south of old US1) from trees in and beside large grassy field; no BHVI at stop 12 (formerly regular here before clear-cutting); this year is the first with hearing aids, which increased detection of distant birds and BGGN
notes: large area along Moncure Flatwood Road, formerly mature pines, had been clearcut, but with remaining seed trees and scattered shrubs
